# Investigation Workflow

Collect Image
      ↓
Observe Every Visible Detail
      ↓
Identify Visual Clues
      ↓
Analyze Surroundings
      ↓
Compare Multiple Public Sources
      ↓
Cross Verify Findings
      ↓
Document Results


# Challenges

While performing image geolocation, investigators may encounter:

* Poor image quality
* Missing landmarks
* Similar-looking locations
* Outdated surroundings
* Seasonal changes
* Edited or cropped images

These challenges highlight why patience and careful observation are essential.


# Best Practices

* Observe before searching.
* Never jump to conclusions.
* Analyze every visible clue.
* Verify findings through multiple sources.
* Respect privacy and ethical guidelines.
* Document observations clearly.

